{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, the current model output can offer far richer information than the sole occurrence probabilities.",
    "However, to be actually useful for territorial management practices, the scale at which we trained should be probably downscaled at a finer resolution.",
    "The second element where our ENN can be further improved in terms of spatial structure has to do with the geomorphological significance of a lattice when used to model landslides.",
    "Such geomorphological processes, in fact, do not follow a regular gridded structure.",
    "In other words, when geoscientists go to the field, they do not see grids, whether they are a few centimeters or the 1 km scale of our model."
  ]
}